sub_title: Frontend Engineer at Warner Bros. Discovery
summary:
I started to use computer since I was five years old. That time it was soviet production machine with running Norton commander on it. Since then, I picked up my interest in programming and decided to study it. After All, this became my career and thing I really love to do.

Today I am working as a software developer where I use newly released technologies and keep myself updated. I have a chance to implement my skills in a production and sharpen them with new challenges that gives me great interest to work with. 

It always fascinates me how trends changes so frequently and something considered as impossible in several years back, now widely used choice for software developers. Therefor I always like to try something new, learn new things.
